<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-184-063 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 533 546</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  April 1 1991 n414 p3(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>DOS 5 debuts in June: beta testing for product nearly complete.andO;(MS/DOS 5.0)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Shore, Joel.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Microsoft MS-DOS 5.0 beta testers report that the product is cleanand almost ready for production, as the Jun 1991 delivery datacomes closer.andP;  Sources familiar with Microsoft's marketingstrategy confirm that the upgrade product will be marketed with alist price of less than $100.andP;  A Microsoft insider has previouslydescribed the rollout as second only to Windows 3.0 in terms ofcomplexity.andP;  The beta-test program was the largest in history fora piece of software.andP;  The few problems that remain have beentraced to other vendors' software or misunderstandings by betatesters regarding configuration parameters.andP;  The installationprocedure is still the subject of heated debate.andP;  A consciousdecision was made to automate the process, making it easier foreven novice users.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Microsoft Corp. (Products).andO;Ticker:    MSFT.andO;Product:   MS-DOS 5.0 (Operating system) (Design and construction).andO;Topic:     Beta TestingOperating Systems.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>